<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1760,2038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,336,1832,1858]" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">Remarks—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pesic, 2004" authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2004" box="[336,735,1832,1858]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[336,599,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">Monatractides persicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A." box="[606,735,1832,1858]" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref8506" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A. (2004) Water mite species of the genus Monatractides K. Viets (Acari, Hydrachnidia, Torrenticolidae) from Iran, with the description of two new species. Zootaxa, 673, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2004">Pešić, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a stream in 
<collectingRegion box="[1097,1170,1832,1858]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">Elburs</collectingRegion>
mountain of North 
<collectingCountry box="[1391,1436,1832,1858]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A." box="[159,415,1868,1894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref8506" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A. (2004) Water mite species of the genus Monatractides K. Viets (Acari, Hydrachnidia, Torrenticolidae) from Iran, with the description of two new species. Zootaxa, 673, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2004">Pešić &amp; Saboori 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Later on, this species was placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walter, 1924)" baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1032,1328,1868,1894]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stadleri">
<emphasis box="[1032,1156,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">M. stadleri</emphasis>
(Walter, 1924)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Asadi, M. &amp; Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I." pageId="9" pageNumber="434" pagination="43 - 55" refId="ref7401" refString="Asadi, M., Pesic, V. &amp; Etemadi, I. (2010) A revised survey of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Iran: new synonyms and descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 2628, 43 - 55." type="journal article" year="2010">
Asadi 
<emphasis box="[151,202,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter authors felt that some differences such as the presence of knob-shaped protrusions at the margin of the gnathosomal bay are not suitable for separating the two species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1760,2038]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,150,321]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">
The specimen from Northern 
<collectingCountry box="[538,583,1976,2002]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">Iran</collectingCountry>
used in this study for molecular analysis perfectly matches the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2004" box="[181,311,2013,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[181,311,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">M. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[822,945,2012,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stadleri">
<emphasis box="[822,945,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="434">M. stadleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a relatively thicker chelicera (ratio L/H 5.6–5.9 
<emphasis box="[372,395,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">vs</emphasis>
. 6.2–6.4, data taken from 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A." box="[708,968,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref8506" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Saboori, A. (2004) Water mite species of the genus Monatractides K. Viets (Acari, Hydrachnidia, Torrenticolidae) from Iran, with the description of two new species. Zootaxa, 673, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2004">Pešić &amp; Saboori 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Based on our COI tree, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">Monatractides persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a sister taxon of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[463,586,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stadleri">
<emphasis box="[463,586,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">M. stadleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[645,712,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,248,1267,1291]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,613,1231]" captionTargetId="figure-203@11.[151,1435,597,1243]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neighbor-joining tree based on studied Monatractides COI sequences. The optimal tree with the sum of branch length = 0.33301736 is shown. The analysis involved 9 nucleotide sequences. There were a total of 669 positions in the final dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794946" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794946/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). The average K2P genetic distance between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2004" box="[1221,1351,187,212]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1351,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">M. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stadleri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">M. stadleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was estimated to 9.35%. Thus, the morphological and molecular data suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pesic &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2004" box="[1190,1322,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1322,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">M. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species distinct from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[390,513,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stadleri">
<emphasis box="[390,513,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="435">M. stadleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
